.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Community \- NIP\-72 moderated communities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Community;
\&
\&    # Define a community
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Community\->community(
\&        pubkey      => $owner_pubkey,
\&        identifier  => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,
\&        name        => \*(AqMy Community\*(Aq,
\&        description => \*(AqA place for discussion\*(Aq,
\&        image       => [\*(Aqhttps://example.com/banner.jpg\*(Aq, \*(Aq1200x400\*(Aq],
\&        moderators  => [
\&            { pubkey => $mod_pubkey, relay => \*(Aqwss://relay1\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&        relays      => [
\&            { url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq, marker => \*(Aqrequests\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Post to a community (top\-level, kind 1111)
\&    my $post = Net::Nostr::Community\->post(
\&        pubkey           => $user_pubkey,
\&        content          => \*(AqHello community!\*(Aq,
\&        community_pubkey => $owner_pubkey,
\&        community_d      => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Reply to a post (nested, kind 1111)
\&    my $reply = Net::Nostr::Community\->reply(
\&        pubkey           => $user_pubkey,
\&        content          => \*(AqGreat post!\*(Aq,
\&        community_pubkey => $owner_pubkey,
\&        community_d      => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,
\&        parent_id        => $parent_event_id,
\&        parent_pubkey    => $parent_author,
\&        parent_kind      => \*(Aq1111\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Approve a post (moderator action, kind 4550)
\&    my $approval = Net::Nostr::Community\->approval(
\&        pubkey           => $mod_pubkey,
\&        community_pubkey => $owner_pubkey,
\&        community_d      => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,
\&        post             => $post_event,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse a community or approval event
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Community\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->name;  # \*(AqMy Community\*(Aq
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-72 moderated communities (Reddit\-style). Communities are
defined by kind 34550 addressable events that list moderators, relays, and
metadata. Users post to communities using kind 1111 (NIP\-22) events with
community\-scoped tags. Moderators approve posts with kind 4550 events.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag of a community definition MAY double as its name, but if a
\&\f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR tag is provided, clients SHOULD display it instead.
.PP
Posts use uppercase tags (\f(CW\*(C`A\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`K\*(C'\fR) for root scope (the community)
and lowercase tags (\f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR) for the parent. For top\-level
posts, both sets point to the community itself.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Community\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Community\*(C'\fR object. Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Community\->new(
\&        identifier  => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,
\&        name        => \*(AqMy Community\*(Aq,
\&        description => \*(AqA place for discussion.\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`image\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`moderators\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR), \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR),
\&\f(CW\*(C`communities\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR), \f(CW\*(C`post_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`post_coordinate\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`post_author\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`post_kind\*(C'\fR. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS community
.IX Subsection "community"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Community\->community(
\&        pubkey      => $hex_pubkey,           # required
\&        identifier  => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,        # required (d tag)
\&        name        => \*(AqDisplay Name\*(Aq,        # optional (SHOULD)
\&        description => \*(AqAbout this place\*(Aq,    # optional
\&        image       => [\*(Aqurl\*(Aq, \*(Aq800x600\*(Aq],    # optional (with optional dims)
\&        moderators  => [                      # optional
\&            { pubkey => $pk, relay => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&        relays      => [                      # optional (MAY)
\&            { url => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq, marker => \*(Aqrequests\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&        extra_tags  => [[\*(Aqrules\*(Aq, \*(Aq...\*(Aq]],    # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 34550 community definition Net::Nostr::Event.
.PP
Moderator entries become \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags with the \f(CW\*(C`moderator\*(C'\fR role. The relay
field is optional per moderator. Relay entries become \f(CW\*(C`relay\*(C'\fR tags with
an optional marker (\f(CW\*(C`author\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`requests\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`approvals\*(C'\fR).
.SS post
.IX Subsection "post"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Community\->post(
\&        pubkey           => $hex_pubkey,       # required
\&        content          => \*(AqHello!\*(Aq,          # required
\&        community_pubkey => $community_owner,  # required
\&        community_d      => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,    # required
\&        relay            => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq,       # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1111 top\-level post to a community. Both uppercase and
lowercase NIP\-22 tags point to the community definition, as specified
by the NIP.
.SS reply
.IX Subsection "reply"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Community\->reply(
\&        pubkey           => $hex_pubkey,       # required
\&        content          => \*(AqI agree!\*(Aq,        # required
\&        community_pubkey => $community_owner,  # required
\&        community_d      => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,    # required
\&        parent_id        => $event_id,         # required
\&        parent_pubkey    => $parent_pk,        # required
\&        parent_kind      => \*(Aq1111\*(Aq,            # required
\&        relay            => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq,       # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1111 nested reply. Uppercase tags point to the community
definition (root scope), lowercase tags point to the parent post or reply.
.SS approval
.IX Subsection "approval"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Community\->approval(
\&        pubkey           => $mod_pubkey,       # required
\&        community_pubkey => $community_owner,  # required (or use communities)
\&        community_d      => \*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq,    # required (or use communities)
\&        post             => $post_event,       # required
\&        relay            => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq,       # optional
\&        approve_via      => \*(Aqe\*(Aq,               # optional: \*(Aqe\*(Aq, \*(Aqa\*(Aq, or \*(Aqboth\*(Aq
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 4550 approval event. The \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR is the JSON\-stringified
post event. The approval MUST include a community \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag, a post reference
(\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag), the post author\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag, and a \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag with the
post kind.
.PP
For replaceable events, \f(CW\*(C`approve_via\*(C'\fR controls how the post is referenced:
.ie n .IP """e"" (default) \- approve this specific version" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWe\fR (default) \- approve this specific version" 4
.IX Item "e (default) - approve this specific version"
.PD 0
.ie n .IP """a"" \- authorize the author to make future changes" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWa\fR \- authorize the author to make future changes" 4
.IX Item "a - authorize the author to make future changes"
.ie n .IP """both"" \- approve current version and authorize changes" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWboth\fR \- approve current version and authorize changes" 4
.IX Item "both - approve current version and authorize changes"
.PD
.PP
For approving a post across multiple communities:
.PP
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Community\->approval(
\&        pubkey      => $mod_pubkey,
\&        communities => [
\&            { pubkey => $pk1, d => \*(Aqcomm1\*(Aq, relay => \*(Aqwss://r1\*(Aq },
\&            { pubkey => $pk2, d => \*(Aqcomm2\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&        post        => $post_event,
\&    );
.Ve
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Community\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 34550 or 4550 event. Returns a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Community\*(C'\fR
object with accessors, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the event kind is not recognized.
.PP
For kind 34550 (community definition), the returned object has
\&\f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`image\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`moderators\*(C'\fR,
and \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR accessors.
.PP
For kind 4550 (approval), the returned object has \f(CW\*(C`communities\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`post_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`post_coordinate\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`post_author\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`post_kind\*(C'\fR
accessors.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Community\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that an event is a well\-formed NIP\-72 event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 34550 or 4550
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 34550 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 4550 missing community \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag (34550:...)
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 4550 missing \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag for the post
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 4550 missing \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag for the post author
.SS community_filter
.IX Subsection "community_filter"
.Vb 4
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::Community\->community_filter(
\&        identifiers => [\*(Aqmy\-community\*(Aq],
\&        authors     => [$owner_pk],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Returns a hashref filter for querying community definitions.
.SS approval_filter
.IX Subsection "approval_filter"
.Vb 4
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::Community\->approval_filter(
\&        community => \*(Aq34550:pubkey:identifier\*(Aq,
\&        authors   => [$mod_pk],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Returns a hashref filter for querying approval events.
.SS legacy_post_filter
.IX Subsection "legacy_post_filter"
.Vb 3
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::Community\->legacy_post_filter(
\&        community => \*(Aq34550:pubkey:identifier\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Returns a hashref filter for querying legacy kind 1 posts tagged with a
community. Clients MAY use this for backwards compatibility but SHOULD NOT
create new kind 1 posts for communities.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
These are available on objects returned by "from_event".
.SS identifier
.IX Subsection "identifier"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $info\->identifier;
.Ve
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag value (community definition).
.SS name
.IX Subsection "name"
.Vb 1
\&    my $name = $info\->name;  # or undef
.Ve
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR tag value, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR. When \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR, the \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR MAY
be used as a display name.
.SS description
.IX Subsection "description"
.Vb 1
\&    my $desc = $info\->description;  # or undef
.Ve
.PP
The community description, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS image
.IX Subsection "image"
.Vb 1
\&    my $img = $info\->image;  # [\*(Aqurl\*(Aq, \*(Aq800x600\*(Aq] or [\*(Aqurl\*(Aq] or undef
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of the image URL and optional dimensions, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS moderators
.IX Subsection "moderators"
.Vb 2
\&    my $mods = $info\->moderators;
\&    # [{ pubkey => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, relay => \*(Aq...\*(Aq }, ...]
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of hashrefs, each with \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR and optional \f(CW\*(C`relay\*(C'\fR.
.SS relays
.IX Subsection "relays"
.Vb 2
\&    my $relays = $info\->relays;
\&    # [{ url => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq, marker => \*(Aqrequests\*(Aq }, ...]
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of hashrefs, each with \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR and optional \f(CW\*(C`marker\*(C'\fR.
.SS communities
.IX Subsection "communities"
.Vb 1
\&    my $comms = $info\->communities;  # [\*(Aq34550:pk:id\*(Aq, ...]
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of community coordinates (from approval events).
.SS post_id
.IX Subsection "post_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $info\->post_id;  # or undef
.Ve
.PP
The approved post\*(Aqs event ID (from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS post_coordinate
.IX Subsection "post_coordinate"
.Vb 1
\&    my $coord = $info\->post_coordinate;  # or undef
.Ve
.PP
The approved post\*(Aqs event coordinate (from non\-community \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag),
or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS post_author
.IX Subsection "post_author"
.Vb 1
\&    my $pk = $info\->post_author;
.Ve
.PP
The approved post author\*(Aqs pubkey (from \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag).
.SS post_kind
.IX Subsection "post_kind"
.Vb 1
\&    my $kind = $info\->post_kind;  # \*(Aq1111\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
The approved post\*(Aqs kind (from \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag).
